Subject:    canonical names vs. nicknames
From:       <a href="?a=95837785200007&r=1&w=2">jsol () bu-it ! BU ! EDU</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198907">1989-07-30 15:20:14</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626976&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626976&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I just switched BU-CS.BU.EDU's mail address to CS.BU.EDU (huh?). That means
that mail originating on BU-CS.BU.EDU will say it is coming from 
user@CS.BU.EDU. CS.BU.EDU is a nickname for BU-CS.BU.EDU in the domain system
and in the host table. I am getting the hint that some sites can't support
mail from a nickname. What does the RFC say about nicknames?

--jsol

